@'\"! tbl|eqn | mmdoc
'\"macro stdmacro
.ds Vn Version 1.2
.ds Dt 10 Nov 1998
.ds Re Release 1.0
.ds Dp Apr 04 17:39
.ds Dm  Apr  4  200
.ds Xs 33549 6 fglcleardepth.gl
.TH FGLCLEARDEPTH 
.SH NAME
.B "fglClearDepth
\- specify the clear value for the depth buffer

.SH FORTRAN SPECIFICATION
SUBROUTINE \f3fglClearDepth\fP(
REAL*4 \fIdepth\fP )
.nf
.fi

.SH PARAMETERS
.TP \w'\f2depth\fP\ \ 'u 
\f2depth\fP
Specifies the depth value used when the depth buffer is cleared. The
initial value is 1.
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f3fglClearDepth\fP specifies the depth value used by \f3fglClear\fP to clear the depth buffer.
Values specified by \f3fglClearDepth\fP are clamped to the range [0,\ 1].
.SH ERRORS
\f3GL_INVALID_OPERATION\fP is generated if \f3fglClearDepth\fP
is executed between the execution of \f3fglBegin\fP
and the corresponding execution of \f3fglEnd\fP.
.SH ASSOCIATED GETS
\f3fglGet\fP with argument \f3GL_DEPTH_CLEAR_VALUE\fP
.SH SEE ALSO
\f3fglClear\fP
@


